commit_message:
Add support for trove incremental backups

Added extra column to backups tables (under instances
and under backups) that will show Yes / No if the
backup is incremental (ie it has a parent)

When you drill down into backup details we now display
the name of the backup parent if this is an
incremental backup. This is displayed as a link with
the backup name so it is navigable

When you create a new backup you can now specify
an existing backup to use as the parent

Note: At some point we should probably have the
create backup dialog filter the available parents
based on the current selection for the instance.
However, so far I haven't worked out how to make
the backup parent choiceField change dynamically
based on user updates to the instance choiceField

Change-Id: I8bc70805aae50a019da3915f8e7aff25f6a7bbc6
Implements: blueprint trove-incremental-backup

commit_message:
Import fixes from Nova scheduler reviews

Import fixes from the Nova scheduler driver review, based upon
revision 4 of https://review.openstack.org/#/c/103165

- create BaseBaremetalHostManager class
- import and refactor the BaremetalHostManager
- refactor IronicHostManager
- minor updates to ExactMatch filters

Note that this change also adds back in copyright notices from
baremetal_host_manager to the ironic_host_manager to reflect
the common heritage of the code.

Change-Id: Iab0d0f1c05474bf341828a2e5aba95715bf71d82

commit_message:
Put iptables arguments in correct order

iptables requires "-m tcp" in order to load the tcp module before we can
use "-p tcp". Before this change, this commands resulted in "Bad
argument `tcp`" rather than a working config

Change-Id: I41c0a2327fb5e9ff17bb187585faf146aa5506c5

commit_message:
Switch to interfaces.d on Debianish systems.

We now write out network interface configuration in per-interface files
on Debian-like distros, using the newer /etc/network/interfaces.d/
configuration scheme.

Change-Id: I443ac7244f3297586466f55ead38af340f78ce7d

commit_message:
Move updating the BM networks to a new script

Currently, devtest_testenv will write the BM networks stanza into
the TE_DATAFILE, and since you can not run devtest_testenv inside
a test environment since it plays with VMs and so on, it makes it
impossible to change the network topology described by bm-networks.
To make it easy to update in a test environment, move the population
call to a separate script.

Change-Id: Iccc562ad16bf73118739cd4535abfac099834e3e

commit_message:
Add a proper IPv4 sorter for jquery-tablesort

The default implementation provided with tablesorter uses a busted
regex and nonsensical formatter.  Add an explicit IPv4 parser/formatter
to Horizon and use it instead.

Closes-Bug: 1342266
Change-Id: I13c709f6171f8e7214b8a3ef15ddf441806df4c2

commit_message:
Add knobs for setting MAC learning on ports

If the Neutron MAC learning API extension is supported, allow user to enable it
for a port. Also display the current MAC learning state in the Ports table and
Port Detail page.

Change-Id: Ia4c4e9a4116527aae8b5488ff8a75eb4113bb8cf
Implements: blueprint mac-learning-knobs

commit_message:
Made import key pair examples more specific.

Removed image specific ssh examples when using import key pair feature under access and security. Replaced with a single generic example.

Closes-bug: 1326291
Change-Id: I2e941e95d72cbef1da7e597f82b5d4b541efb72b

commit_message:
Fix the auth_uri option in heat.conf

Add the missin /v2.0 suffix for the RHEL-like versions.

Change-Id: I3bc59c00c36d1be07130c4ad742e0a315998ed27
Closes-Bug: 1345814

commit_message:
Fix SQL exception getting statitics with metaquery

In the scenario with mysql as storage backend, when getting statistics
with metaquery, sqlalchemy will raise an exception of "Unknown column
'sample.id' in 'on clause'", this is because of a wrong usage of JOIN
clause.

Change-Id: I6f140952082ab245f27d576ee9629a086104f8b1

[{'created': '2014-07-17 15:54:30.000000000', 'message': 'Remove extra list

We are using "ctlplane" as the first parameter to Fn::Select here, so
the second parameter must be a map, not a list. Fixes the following
error:

ERROR: Property error : BlockStorage0Deployment: input_values Index to
"Fn::Select" must be an integer

Change-Id: I34153543f8c3152df449e1b42e1f76a78a7d6ba3
'}]
commit_message:
Remove extra list

We are using "ctlplane" as the first parameter to Fn::Select here, so
the second parameter must be a map, not a list. Fixes the following
error:

ERROR: Property error : BlockStorage0Deployment: input_values Index to
"Fn::Select" must be an integer

Change-Id: I34153543f8c3152df449e1b42e1f76a78a7d6ba3

Flavor CRUD v2

To use the low level api for the resource:

    from openstack.compute.v2 import flavor
    resp = flavor.Flavor.get_data_by_id(sess, '102')

The resp will be a dictionary.

Change-Id: I3a835e4e7ea5dd6e62cdd91748589edf54c0dcf9
"}]
commit_message:
Full flavor CRUD

Flavor CRUD v2

To use the low level api for the resource:

    from openstack.compute.v2 import flavor
    resp = flavor.Flavor.get_data_by_id(sess, '102')

The resp will be a dictionary.

Change-Id: I3a835e4e7ea5dd6e62cdd91748589edf54c0dcf9

commit_message:
Adds starting point for Architecture and Design Guide

The areas that still need work are:
- needs double-checking for tables
- see http://docs.openstack.org/arc/OpenStackArchitectureDesignGuide.epub
  for intended structure

commit_message:
Remove deprecated commands from shell

Remove all deprecated commands from the shell
since they are no longer used and to keep
the command line menu from looking cluttered.

Change-Id: I4ebf13fd5ace6b72d2d76f9793dcc2ced1acfb9b

Delete unused class Service

The base class 'Service' in tempest/__init__ seems not to be used any
longer due to various reworks in the code.

Change-Id: I491293e4adf8239f1426baa5432aad4f67001ac0

commit_message:
Remove deprecated commands from shell

Remove all deprecated commands from the shell 
since they are no longer used and to keep
the command line menu from looking cluttered.

Fixes-Bug: #1314218

Change-Id: I83eb3bc304f4cea1b652bbd8310ade615e3140c9

subject: Default auth_version to v3.0

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

commit_message:
Default auth_version to v3.0

Default auth_version to 'v3.0' as the token information is backward
compatible. This change will not affect PKI tokens as it is being
validated locally.

Change-Id: I9812ab10fc3a8ca411ff46d25848f9ac5af4592d
Closes-Bug: #1336056

commit_message:
Sync time on nodes before checking Ceph health

System test 'ceph_ha' almost always fails while
checking ceph health due to clock skew. That's
why an additional time synchronization and restart
of Ceph service was added to the test.

Change-Id: I58af30d29399c70b9f5d142d3c495710f05994f2
Closes-bug: #1336233

Hola Eoghan,

> @cdent: thanks for this. I'm thinking it's pretty much good to land, except for the open
> question on Current versus Power.

I asked Haomeng about that (on the producer-side review: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/72538/ ) and the gist that they are using the names as driven by the ipmitool output. Some of the power related sensors are current, some are power, but they have the _name_ current. So if there is a bug, it is in the ipmitool and it would be complex (in the sense of too many participants) to manage mappings from "bad ipmitool" to good Ironic+Ceilometer.

> Would you be happy to punt that issue to a later patch?

So yeah, I think it is probably best to save it for later. When both the producer and consumer sides are integrated I suspect there could well be quite a few changes required, but we'll only know from some real world feedback.

So I think we can say go, although I was hoping to get some review from Lucas (thus his CC on the reviewer list).'}, {'account_id': 2284, 'date': '2014-07-19 14:23:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 12: Code-Review+2

Thanks for the response, Chris.

I think we should go ahead, land this now, and assume that the "bad impitool" aspect can be addressed later (even subsequent to juno-2 would be fine to change this IMO, given that milestones are relatively arbitrary points in the development cycle, that don't really carry the same sense of on-going support as would a full release).

Cheers,

It would be good to somehow shrink the huge amount of that data. As I saw, it would worth a try to generate the most of them in a loop or within a bunch of loops. Or if not, then at least to store it separated from the actual tests, to make that file more readable. BTW do we need all that test data? I mean that you check in details only one sample from sometimes ten.

[{'created': '2014-07-08 15:21:36.000000000', 'message': "Implement consuming ipmi notifications from Ironic

This borrows heavily from the compute notifications code. The basic
idea is that there are a few classes of samples that can be had
(Fan, Temperature, Voltage, Current). Within these are potentially
multiple individual sensors and values. In all cases the volume and
unit of a sample can always be extracted from the value of a
'Sensor Reading' key. The volume is cast to a float. If the value
is 'Disabled' the data is dropped.

Each subclass exists to allow flexible handling via stevedore, but
all activity is performed in the superclass.

The supplied test data is the currently blessed sample from the
Ironic team.

Identifier and name construction is worth a close look because this
is an area of frequent discussion:

* resource_id is composed from node_uuid and sensor id
* meter name is based on the class name and is generic, only
  paired with a resource_id does it identify a specific sensor
* unit is parsed out of sensor data but may not be consistent
  with units used elsewher in ceilometer

Questions (this section to be removed before review is finalized):

* How much of the payload should be kept?
* Is unit handling okay?
* Are the meter names appropriate?
* This is clearly not enough but wanted to start the review early;
  what else is needed.

Change-Id: Ie7ac92aebb45fc23d6134b4d6693f8a1e4d4ea40

commit_message:
Implement consuming ipmi notifications from Ironic

This borrows heavily from the compute notifications code. The basic
idea is that there are few classes of samples that can be had
(Fan, Temperature, Voltage, Current). Within these are potentially
multiple individual sensors and values. In all cases the volume and
unit of a sample can always be extracted from the value of a
'Sensor Reading' key. The volume is cast to a float. If the value
is 'Disabled' the data is dropped.

Each subclass exists to allow flexible handling via stevedore, but
all activity is performed in the superclass.

The supplied good test data is the currently blessed sample from the
Ironic team. The bad test data tickles either skipping missing data or
producing warnings in the log.

Identifier and name construction is worth a close look because this
is an area of frequent discussion:

* resource_id is composed from node_uuid and sensor id
* meter name is based on the class name and is generic, only
  paired with a resource_id does it identify a specific sensor
* unit is parsed out of sensor data and mapped to SI units

Change-Id: Ie7ac92aebb45fc23d6134b4d6693f8a1e4d4ea40
Implements blueprint ironic-notifications

commit_message:
Symlink register-nodes into scripts, and use it

os-cloud-config now includes an register-nodes script, replacing
the one shipping in this repository. To make use of it, symlink
it into scripts so it's in the PATH and update the call in
setup-baremetal to use the new options, as well as removing the old
shell based script to avoid confusing git and developers.

Change-Id: I0ec217ee1d20ee02fc51c30d1d2d2529bb4b3d47

commit_message:
Add qa spec for bp:stress-api-tracking

This patch adds the qa spec file for the
stress-api-tracking blueprint.

It has been expanded to include the tracking of api
calls from any tempest test, not just the stress tests.

Partially implements blueprint stress-api-tracking

Change-Id: I744f38612c885b455af0c505696768d716d3918e

commit_message:
Add resource properties to stack-preview

Certain resource details may influence the final price of the
infrastructure being created by a stack (e.g. instance flavors), so this
adds resources properties to the output of stack-preview.

Implements: blueprint stack-preview-details
Change-Id: I6ea892dedfc96aeda8e8a21e67562820fd21c7bb

commit_message:
Removed deprecated command from glance cli

Member-add is no longer a command in python-glanceclient and
should be removed since it has been deprecated. We are removing
all the deprecated glance client commands in this patch 
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/98862/.

commit_message:
Mark the 'check_vX_token' methods deprecated

The check_v2_token and check_v3_token perform the same work as
the corresponding validate_vX_token methods on the provider
api. The validate methods are used in favor of the check methods.

This patchset marks the check methods as deprecated, slated for
removal in the K cycle.

Change-Id: I717dd93ce359439af238dcf1f3349e9477e6b82b
bp: non-persistent-tokens

commit_message:
Hard-link multiple identical files.

Venv creation leaves multiple files around with the same contents.
This element consolidates all the identical files down to a single,
multiply-hardlinked copy.

It should honour identical files with different ownerships.

Change-Id: I2cb9e4e678940cce2faf199af541c4069c9b0f3f

commit_message:
Split up metering test case into plugin + test case

Currently the metering test case includes setUp code as well
as the tests themselves. Splitting up the test case class
into two allows other test cases to inherit the metering
plugin class without inherting (And implicitly re-running)
the tests themselves.

Closes-Bug: #1336198
Change-Id: I4427fcd17cc3d28189f9f74df487084cf35c1634

commit_message:
Removing references of out-of-date versions of OpenStack

Ignored glossary and bk-openstack-security-guide.xml
Removed Grizzly 'workaround' link from ch_compute.xml
Removed Grizzly reference from ch_database-access-control.xml
Removed Grizzly reference from ch_database-sccess-control.xml
Updated link to Icehouse release notes in ch_management-interfaces.xml
Rreworded the sentence to be descriptive ch_networking-services.xml
Updated Grizzly reference to Icehouse in ch_networking-services.xml
Restructured sentence in ch_networking-services.xml
Updated Havana to Icehouse concerning FWaaS in ch_networking-sevices.xml
Removed Grizzly ref & restructured sentence ch_state-of-networking.xml

Change-Id: Idb1416148e8c3182b057d7f010a455a5fb7e956c
Closes-Bug: #1343562

commit_message:
Fix last of direct use of object modules

This replaces all uses of nova.objects.<module>.<object> with
nova.objects.<object> in the remaining places.

Implements-Blueprint: object-subclassing

Change-Id: Ic7632cca2455a38abcbdb94feb7e39cfb898bb27

commit_message:
Allow for optional properties

At least for some header values, some properties may need to be
optional. The rigid value-or-exception way doesn't work nicely with a
few things in swift related headers, especially on objects, where several
header values are optional.

Change-Id: I58cc95eedd79fdceb398058ba8ccc75a8d76bd82

With regards to the virt/netutils.py parameter changes should we also add (or update) the unit tests in tests/network/test_network_info.py to test for this?

If I understand things correctly you needed to change this for XenServer... but if we ever removed or changed the XenServer test code my concern is this would no longer be covered.'}, {'account_id': 475, 'date': '2014-07-14 18:45:38.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

So the parameter defaults had to be moved into the function to make sure that the tests had a chance to override the values.

This is a case where the code has to be made to support testing, not that the code was wrong, per-se.

So, yes, if the tests were removed, we'd no longer need coverage for this, but we'd also no longer _need_ coverage because we weren't using that case anymore either. (The next person who writes a test that needs it, will quickly find out it doesn't work...)

So if I were to add this test, I'd be writing a test to ensure that future tests work properly...not something I'm too keen on. Too meta :-)"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-14 18:45:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: -Verified

commit_message:
xenapi: Use netuils.get_injected_network_template

The Xen driver duplicates quite a bit of code used to inject the `interfaces`
template into the guest.

This patch makes the Xen driver use the generic `netutils` version.

Parameter defaults were moved from the signature into the method since in the
original code, you wouldn't be able to override them due to their value being
populated at import-time, not run-time.

Change-Id: I4cd1631b8e6ec2dc3fae1f8eb0362aecead53f1e

I think you're suggesting the API should return a failure for events without a host, which is pretty much what the code is currently doing already.

This pretty much means in my opinion abandoning this patch, handling the failure in neutron, and then implementing a mechanism to find which events were not processed because of the failure.

I would like to find a way to avoid all this churn. Would it be acceptable to modify  the return value compute_api.external_instance_event so that before building the response in https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/api/openstack/compute/contrib/server_external_events.py#L135 status would be set to 'failed' for all events which triggered an error?
I'm not sure whether in that case the POST operation should still return a 200 or should instead return a 500 or other error code. Personally I think 200 is OK - because the event resource was correctly created, even if then its execution then failed."}, {'account_id': 261, 'date': '2014-07-16 16:38:38.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-16 16:38:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-07-01 12:38:21.000000000', 'message': "Do not dispatch events for instances without host

In some cases Neutron might send events such as 'VIF unplugged'
for instances which are either being deleted or shelved. When
that happens there will be a failure in dispatching the event
to the appropriate compute node - as there is no host for the
instance.

As multiple neutron events can be stashed in a single call
it is important to avoit that this kind of errors will prevent
processing of other events in the same call.

This patch does the following:
- Avoid event processing for instances without a host.
  In this case there will be indeed no host where the event
  could be dispatched for processing.
- Ensure exceptions raised while dispatching events over RPC API
  to a a given host will not prevent processing of other events.

Unit tests for these additional checks have been added. A minimal
refactoring of unit test has been performed in order to minimize
code duplication.

Change-Id: I18062b81e50c722ec96b4296ac39384493683ae3
Closes-Bug: #1333654

"}, {'created': '2014-07-16 16:38:38.000000000', 'message': "Ensure all external events are always processed

In some cases Neutron might send events such as 'VIF unplugged'
for instances which are either being deleted or shelved. When
that happens there will be a failure in dispatching the event
to the appropriate compute node - as there is no host for the
instance.

As multiple neutron events can be stashed in a single call
it is important to avoid that this kind of errors will prevent
processing of other events in the same call.

This patch does the following:
- Avoid dispatching events for instances without a host to the
  RPC layer.
  In this case there will be indeed no host where the event
  could be dispatched for processing.
- Ensure exceptions raised while dispatching events over RPC API
  to a a given host will not prevent processing of other events.

If any of the above happens, the create event request will return
a 207 response code. For specific events, a 422 unprocessable
entity code will be set in the former case, whereas a 500
internal server error will be set in the latter.

This patch also preserve the characteristic that events are
returned in the response in the same order they were found in
the request.

Unit tests for these additional checks have been added. A minimal
refactoring of unit test has been performed in order to minimize
code duplication.

Change-Id: I18062b81e50c722ec96b4296ac39384493683ae3
Closes-Bug: #1333654

returned in the response in the same order they were found in
the request.

Unit tests for these additional checks have been added. A minimal
refactoring of unit test has been performed in order to minimize
code duplication.

commit_message:
Do not process events for instances without host

In some cases Neutron might send events such as 'VIF unplugged'
for instances which are either being deleted or shelved. When
that happens there will be a failure in dispatching the event
to the appropriate compute node - as there is no host for the
instance.

As multiple neutron events can be stashed in a single call
it is important to avoid that this kind of errors will prevent
processing of other events in the same call.

This patch does not process events for instances without a host,
marking them as failed.

When the above condition occurs, the create event request will
return a 207 response code. For specific events, a 422
unprocessable entity code will be set.

This patch also preserve the characteristic that events are
returned in the response in the same order they were found in
the request.

Change-Id: I18062b81e50c722ec96b4296ac39384493683ae3
Closes-Bug: #1333654

commit_message:
Use resource discovery for Network Services

This change migrates the network services pollsters to
leverage resource discovery through pipeline yaml. This
will also be more HA friendly to distribute work across
multiple central agents.

Change-Id: I4d454e98974438438c166051451b76ce9fbbc2a4

commit_message:
Implicitly ignore attributes that are mapped to None in LDAP

Attributes that are mapped to None in LDAP trigger a 500 error when
performing a search if they are not explicitly ignored in keystone's
configuration.  These attributes should always be ignored, even if
the admin left the attribute out of the ignore list.

Change-Id: Ibbabdd0013059d5720250816764021a0b3ce8ce0
Closes-bug: #1335437

commit_message:
Remove sshd reconfig from lib/ironic

The sshd reconfiguration to listen on port 2222 provides no
benefit and complicates deployment on some systems.  This removes
the reconfiguration and instead just confirms SSH connectivity.
Default SSH host and ports are left configurable, but the port now
reflects the default 22.

Change-Id: Iaf7c71854c3741a505a79037ffb8c86ace74fc27
(cherry picked from commit 867651049a07a087e619a17d05f569188032f7e0)

(2 comments)

I've no problem with the idea so my comments are largely nits.

Obviously, the x_delete_* parameters are not protected by the signature. I don't see this matters...if you managed to capture a signature, re-playing the operation with an empty file is just as damaging as setting x-delete_after=1.

I'm curious why you picked X-Delete-At/After as being useful? If your intent was to allow setting of all useful attributes, should you not also enable Content-Encoding?

Looking at the code, it looks like you can set content-type in the form, yet this is not documented. Would it be useful to document that as one of the optional fields (assuming I'm correct)?"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-15 17:32:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: -Verified

commit_message:
Add X-Delete-At/After support to FormPost

This change adds the ability to specify a X-Delete-At or
X-Delete-After attribute when using the FormPost middleware.

Here is an example of what you need to add to the form:

  <input type="hidden" name="x_delete_at" value="<unix-timestamp>"/>
  <input type="hidden" name="x_delete_after" value="<seconds>"/>

To be inline with the other form imput names, x-delete-at/after has
changed to x_delete_at/after.

DocImpact
Change-Id: Ib1cc0bcf1dd7d2b689f2f26d100f9bab36880c81
Closes-Bug: #1065522

commit_message:
Initial implementation of validator

This is the initial implementation of a jsonschema type
validator for the Keystone API. Something very similar to this is used
in Nova V3 for validation. By using jsonschema to validate API requests,
we can make parameters that are passed in fit the criteria we allow and
what is specified in the Identify API spec. This will also allow us to
validate parameters by wrapping the method that needs validation.

bp: api-validation
Change-Id: I1e1dc8e5ac3ad766f05444b16d56a22c89602b9f

If this doesn't make sense, please ping clarkb in #openstack-infra for more information."}, {'account_id': 7787, 'date': '2014-07-18 18:42:05.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Kyle, 

If we require a new version of alembic, why don't we bump up the requirements to reflect that?"}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-07-19 08:05:13.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

We often forget to check the minimum version of requirements. The requirements should be synced with actual requirements (in this case alembic should be >=0.6.4). Ideally this version bump should be discussed before the corresponding neutron patch was merged.

This topic is not directly related to third party CI. I don't think fresh installation of Python modules is not a requirement on third party CI infra, but third party CI maintainers can avoid unnecessary failures by fresh installation.

IMO this version bump sounds reasonable. According to alembic changes of 0.6.4 looks safe and 0.6.5 has been tested well so far."}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-07-19 08:09:26.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

One addition: If we don't bump the minimum requrement of alembic, it means that neutron db migration healing should work with alembic 0.6.3, but I don't think it is not a right way to address the problem. Even though it is found by third party CI failure, it is not a problem of CI setup.

On the other hand, I agree opinions from Kyle and Clarkb that third party CI should run with the latest version since it is done in OpenStack upstream CI and it would avoid unnecessary differences in running environments."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-20 19:03:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: -Verified

commit_message:
Bump alembic to 0.6.4 for Neutron

Recently merged neutron healing migration
(https://review.openstack.org/#/c/96438/)
needs alembic >= 0.6.4 for mysql.

The relevant fix in alembic:
    https://bitbucket.org/zzzeek/alembic/commits/b29780719904

Change-Id: If67241592ba82aed3b41b4acec17bd8d604a3c4b
Partial-Bug: #1342507

commit_message:
Fix accepting longer PKI keystone auth requests to Barbican

Passing CLI option '-b' during barbican start is not honored by uwsgi.
So, set buffer-size=65535 in /etc/barbican/vassals/barbican-api.ini
Removed redundant '--logto' CLI option to uwsgi.

Change-Id: Icea0144f2c19e916d65c9836ddc9d7e48ecd9412

commit_message:
Live migration failed with UnboundLocalError

Related to patch I2755c59b4db736151000dae351fd776d3c15ca39

Currently, live migration will be failed when using shared instance
path with QCOW2 because of a UnboundLocalError caused by referencing
to 'instance_dir'.

The fix was changing the logic of _create_images_and_backing() only
in the condition of not is_shared_instance_path and not
is_shared_block_storage.

Change-Id: I935a3b005659205df7fcf90945e9e9072eb6beda
Closes-Bug: #1346816

commit_message:
Add admin guide chapter for Ceilometer/Telemetry

The Telemetry chapter was previously missing from the admin guide. This
patch adds an xml file for introducing a new chapter for this component
and also contains five main sections in the form of new files.

It will require several patch sets to fill all sections with content.
This patch contains partial content in the first two sections, namely
the System Architecture and the Data Collection.

Implements: blueprint add-ceilometer-admin-guide-to-openstack-manuals
Change-Id: Ibce86fe27e3d08346c42080c426716e6f04dc90c

Set any_order to True in some unit tests

In some tested methods iteritems() is used, and order of returned items
may be different (belongs on PYTHONHASHSEED).

commit_message:
Update comment related to NSX connector type

- Comment in parentheses was inteded to tell user which values he can
  use for connector type when it was a text edit field.  Right now NSX
  connector type appears as dropdown list and comment is not usefull any
  longer. Zap it.

Change-Id: Ia42508d3be59ae3ffa541d4c1dad66aa2cff0816

This reverts commit 7916d6cb041960750604e91dd768f03700ff845d and
commit 7c6ea39940380738b4b969ed4c1b11e45ecd2055.

commit_message:
Revert oslo.messaging 1.4.0.0a3 and oslo.config 1.4.0.0a2

This reverts commit 7916d6cb041960750604e91dd768f03700ff845d and
commit 7c6ea39940380738b4b969ed4c1b11e45ecd2055.

The oslo alpha releases are only published as wheels because we
don't want to expose them to icehouse users who may still be using
pip 1.3 which doesn't know to ignore alphas.

We recently switched to bandersnatch based pypi mirror to allow
us to mirror these wheels.

However, the py26 unit test jobs on centos6 are failing because
an old version of virtualenv and pip is installed. The failure looks
like:

  Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement oslo.config>=1.4.0.0a2

Monty has been working on a fix, but it's proving to be a whack-a-mole
situation with each fix showing up yet another issue. Let's remove
the alphas for now so that the auto-proposing bot isn't proposing
changes which we know are going to fail.

Change-Id: I52c695086b90a94eab2ab92533665b44f00b9077

commit_message:
Base class for scenario test using Tempest clients

Define a very simple base class for migrating all scenario
tests to using tempest own clients.
This patch is the first step required to allow us to migrate
all tests one by one in dedicated changes, and finally drop
the unused Official Client pieces once migration is complete.

The various functions that are available in the OfficialClientTest
shall be migrated if / when needed by a specific test.

Change-Id: Ie82c8d8628ab50d6461a756713d56f78a2daa1dd
Partially-implements: bp:tempest-client-scenarios

commit_message:
Upgrades, fix OSTF checker

Right now we don't have enabled authorization
by default, fixed OSTF checker to work with
both versions of OSTF, where authorization is
enabled and where it is disabled.

Change-Id: Icc52695a7a619ada15551f1b64f41e581e2bd438
Closes-bug: #1346839

commit_message:
Fix the way of deleting metadata properties

Since glanceclent provides special parameter for removing
metadata, method that does it in murano was updated.
Previos version was not working - the operation finished
without errors, but metadata still presented.

Closes-Bug: #1342749

Change-Id: I493a7a28c6886c948b1c71e10b652d9b7dcdffcb

commit_message:
Move create snapshot to finally block

In case if create diagnostic snapshot failed,
we can not create env snapshot with devops.
To avoid this  - move create snapshot in finally block

Change-Id: I6826930d997006a51ca79b94314f7df3c06b2f66
Closes-Bug: #1325907

[{'created': '2014-07-21 07:40:41.000000000', 'message': 'Fix the request path of Telemetry API v2

Currently, there is no concept of tenant segregation, and the request
path of Telemetry API v2 is "/v2/{resource}" not the
"v2/{tenant_id}/resource", this patch correct it.

Change-Id: I9e7f28ca22ca0d884951c10f65a89b154e041ce2
Closes-Bug: #1343903
'}]
commit_message:
Fix the request path of Telemetry API v2

Currently, there is no concept of tenant segregation, and the request
path of Telemetry API v2 is "/v2/{resource}" not the
"v2/{tenant_id}/resource", this patch correct it.

Change-Id: I9e7f28ca22ca0d884951c10f65a89b154e041ce2
Closes-Bug: #1343903

commit_message:
Add query param to allow nested resource list

Add `nested_depth` param to OpenStack API to allow listing of
nested resources up to `nested_depth` level.

Implements: blueprint explode-nested-resources
Change-Id: I1cd6c35fe7f3eb1c5b67217e38aef53cb0b6ff76

commit_message:
Update django_openstack_auth to 1.1.6

When keystone added pkiz it broke horizon, this version
is required for horizon to continue to work.

Change-Id: I2582d41235783ea160a43f8888035961d6cacd66

commit_message:
Promote libffi-dev as a general dependency

libffi-dev/libffi-devel can be requested for rebuilding the
python clients which is an un-skipable part of the devstack install.

Promoting the libffi-devel to a general dependency.

Change-Id: I1dac7fd536b94de1e49aaf335ac29ffae1bd39d1

commit_message:
Pass user_creds_id into nested stacks

To avoid creating additional user_creds entries for every nested
stack, pass in the parent/owner stack user_creds_id.  This means
updates will work with trust-scoped tokens, and will remove the
overhead of creating a new trust for every nested resource.

This will also avoid the potential situation where a stack has been
updated (adding nested stacks) by a user other than the original
stack owner - if that happened, it would be impossible to delete
the stacks (owner and nested) as any user other than an admin,
due to restrictions on who can delete the trust.

Note the delete logic is modified so nested stacks no longer delete
the user_creds ID.  If we stick with this simple logic, it will
mean it's necessary to either delete all stacks before upgrading
or do a manual DB query to clean up any orphaned user_creds rows
when existing nested stacks are deleted (such a cleanup is probably
already necessary due to the previous patch fixing user_creds
handling for backup stacks)

Also modifies the stub_keystoneclient test call to make stubbing
the client in the parser test easier.

Change-Id: Id1fb89c92af48777b0487015d5048af34b33af76
Closes-Bug: #1342593

This is probably a good idea, but it doesn't actually solve the problem.

validate_template works differently to the other APIs in that it returns a dict that looks like {'Error': 'message'} when it fails, instead of returning an exception. So this bug is caused by an exception being raised outside of the try/except blocks where validate_template generates the error message.

We'll likely still need this change (because Schema was originally intended only for properties, and later got repurposed for parameters) for different APIs, but it doesn't actually solve the problem with this specific one. As Steve pointed out, we'll need to specifically tell heat-cfn-api how to treat the error... and I'm not sure any more how this works for the OpenStack API :D"}, {'account_id': 7385, 'date': '2014-07-08 07:31:53.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Fix serialization of InvalidSchemaError

Move InvalidSchemaError to heat.common.exception and pass a keyword
argument so that it can be serialized properly.

Change-Id: Iada3273b2b0b129bc0125b68fecf1e0efc081611
Closes-Bug: #1336740

commit_message:
Changes wording from "spin it up" to "create an instance"

Recommend changing the wording from spinning up an image, where "instance"
is the specific node running from a base "image."

Change-Id: I0815699d5a74ef57b0449b533ff9c3a131e18cb6
Closes-Bug: #1344324

commit_message:
Allow user to view outputs of failed stacks

Outputs like 'stderr' are designed for users to debug failed stacks, if
users can not view outputs of failed stacks, they can not get the error
messages.

Change-Id: I1b2b4f0e967695cf3297d93022cecec958e94b24
Closes-Bug: #1333208

commit_message:
Adds Content-Type to alarm REST notifier

When doing a POST request in the REST alarm notifier,
we should include a Content-Type: 'application/json' header.

Closes-Bug: #1346147
Change-Id: Ic02c8caeb294763443858dbbb3192e09c594c8cf

commit_message:
Bump up the zake requirement to 0.0.26

Zake was released with a new version with bug fixes
and a addition of the emulation of one more of the
kazoo methods (transaction check support).

This change helps make it possible to test the fix
for bug 1343029 without requiring a full zookeeper
setup to test.

The zake *noteable* changes (for those interested):

- Add travis 3.4 builds
- Add more concurrent transaction tests
- Add much more robust transaction support
- Add basic check transaction support + tests
- Create all parent paths and child paths in the same lock context
- Address concurrent client variable modification
- Move znode making function to storage
- Add link to kazoo readthedocs
- Add test + fix for empty custom versions being provided
- Fix custom version in 'stat' response
- Ensure all paths are normalized before storage interaction

Change-Id: I376bddc78242f2fd559eb80856587c2c4d64b875

commit_message:
Upgrades, remove keystone client from dependencies

Removed keystone client dependencies to prevent
errors, when fuel client and upgrade script use
different versions.

Also it helps to solve the problem with broken
script because keystone client uses pip as
dependencies.

Change-Id: I16b0a6ecfdc4b4b14eac4441d9f1dbc06fa0c13a
Closes-bug: #1346366

Can't you fix this in packstack by using 162 for uid/gid? I think this was added for the Ubuntu case where the uid isn't managed.

If that's not satisfactory then having nova_user_id = undef not create the user and group resources would seem a bit less intrusive and probably a little more palatable for Ubuntu users."}, {'account_id': 11166, 'date': '2014-07-04 08:22:15.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

>Can't you fix this in packstack by using 162 for uid/gid?
>I think this was added for the Ubuntu case where the uid
>isn't managed.
NO! Puppet should not override anything provided by package and there is no guarantee that uid/gid in package won't change.

>If that's not satisfactory then having nova_user_id =
>undef not create the user and group resources would seem a
>bit less intrusive and probably a little more palatable
>for Ubuntu users.
NO! a) do it like other projects for quick example packstack-ceilometer where they have to have user resouce which is being run after the packages and it's done because they actually add him to some groups or b) don't touch the user at all as puppet-nova does not need to do any changes to it by default.

The b) option is more logical as if someone really needs to statically specify uid/gid and need to do other insane magic he can do it. Again different uid/gid does not really matter if you use NFS when you create netgroup for example nova-shared and add nova group to it on all nodes..."}, {'account_id': 11166, 'date': '2014-07-04 08:52:32.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-04 08:52:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

commit_message:
Don't manage the nova uid/gid if nova_{user,group}_id is undef

Any user modification before standard system package creates the
user is wrong. Usecase of patch adding the user is also broken as
there are several other options: provide user before whole class
nova, have user id enforced by package or as most humans do accept
that in multi host enviroments there are 3 layers - user, group and
netgroup. In all cases nova puppet module should never touch the
user as it's provided by package on all supported systems, but for
backwards compatibility the management of user is disabled if
nova_group_id is undef or if nova_user_id is undef.

Closes-Bug: rhbz#1115946
Change-Id: If22b27f5fb78ba6821f4d6e8c275f8b80c70dd59

WIP: Serialise paramiko requests

This may well serve to work around the eventlet problem, until a
permanent fix can be made to eventlet. (Which latter I'm working on
- this is just a quick hack.)

commit_message:
NSX: fix router ports port_security_enabled=False

Previously there was a bug that resulted in a security group being
added to router ports which was not supported in NSX. Removing the
security group didn't actually completely solve the problem as we
never cleared the allowed_address_pairs on the router port. This
patch fixes this issue by disabling port_security_enabled on the
router port.

Change-Id: Ib61756e3bd5866318cbc3bb9856344571399d656
Closes-bug: 1344266
Related-bug: 1329043

commit_message:
Run migrations from only the bootstrap host

This ensures database migrations only happen on one node.  It moves database
migration from post-configure.d to configure.d within individual service
elements and protects all 'db sync' call with an os-is-bootstrap-host check
until we have a better story regarding leadership checks.  Also removes all
redundant 'db sync' calls from the boot-stack element (they were not actually
being run there, anyway).

Change-Id: Idf3c642614699cf3f79aefd7434b3eb4983df1ae
Closes-bug: #1339047

Upgrades, catch http exceptions generated by nailgun client

Sometimes we can get 500 error from
nailgun, in health check we need to
catch all of this exceptions

Closes-bug: #1346346

commit_message:
Use full plugin class paths for Neutron

Neutron database migration utility doesn't support neutron.conf
where core or service plugins are configured via their aliases,
so full plugin class paths are required

This change is required for https://review.openstack.org/#/c/97398
Closes-bug: #1335149

Change-Id: I5ab348be6c9590a9317211178ca4cff4bb152be2

[{'created': '2014-07-03 12:40:15.000000000', 'message': 'Fix virt BDM __setattr__ and __getattr__

Previously we would only allow these to work on fields that are found in
the _proxy_as_attr collection of the object and we would unconditionally
raise an AttributeError otherwise.

This behaviour is too restrictive as it prevents us from using mock on
these objects properly, Instead we now delegate back to the parent
class for a more natural behaviour.

Change-Id: I5c221eef8f05c66ac2e2fb4abf645748407462c0
'}]
commit_message:
Fix virt BDM __setattr__ and __getattr__

Previously we would only allow these to work on fields that are found in
the _proxy_as_attr collection of the object and we would unconditionally
raise an AttributeError otherwise.

This behaviour is too restrictive as it prevents us from using mock on
these objects properly, Instead we now delegate back to the parent
class for a more natural behaviour.

Change-Id: I5c221eef8f05c66ac2e2fb4abf645748407462c0

commit_message:
Add missing foreign key on pci_devices.compute_node_id

The model specifies a foreign key, but no migrations have ever added it.

Closes-Bug: 1342834
Change-Id: Ia9151b5a7389fbb4c39155f7e192c24bd99e7a9a

[{'created': '2014-02-17 14:39:49.000000000', 'message': 'Allow to delegate some tunnel provider attributes choice to neutron

Provide ml2.allow_partial_specs option support for GRE/VXLAN.

In practice, for GRE/VXLAN provider networks provider:segmentation_id
choice can be delegated to neutron, in such case neutron will try to
find a network in tenant network pools which respects provided
provider attributes.

    DocImpact

    Related to blueprint provider-network-partial-specs

Change-Id: I720d7d04f6e3453145e888d9e4d9b5e381d0f7d4

find a network in tenant network pools which respects provided
provider attributes.

    DocImpact

commit_message:
Add partial specs support in ML2 for gre/vxlan provider networks

ML2 provider networks partial specs let admins choose some provider
network attributes and let neutron choose remaining attributes. This
change provides the implementation for GRE/VXLAN provider networks.

In practice, for GRE/VXLAN provider networks provider:segmentation_id
choice can be delegated to neutron, in such case neutron will try to
find a network in tenant network pools which respects provided
provider attributes.

DocImpact

Related to blueprint provider-network-partial-specs
Partial-Bug: #1330562

Change-Id: I720d7d04f6e3453145e888d9e4d9b5e381d0f7d4

commit_message:
Code change for nova support cinder client v2

Use v2 volume endpoint to attach/detach volume would be failed,
due to nova not supporting cinder client v2 yet. This patch is for
nova support cinder client v2.

Implements bp support-cinderclient-v2
Closes-Bug: #1215772

Conflicts:
	nova/volume/cinder.py

Change-Id: I9aa313be9e0b8759b78446613db7b1eae82fdf78

More of a question, but why is this not following the VIF driver pattern used when booting the VM?"}, {'account_id': 1653, 'date': '2013-12-16 12:29:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

@John, when a VM is booted a config spec is created for the VM. This spec will already contain the details of the interfaces that are attached to the VM. This is done here - https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/virt/vmwareapi/vm_util.py#L82
The attach and detach of a NIC are just done by creating an updated configuration spec. If we had to do this at the boot time then it would be an additional VM configuration when the VM is created.
Thanks
Gary'}, {'account_id': 9754, 'date': '2013-12-19 00:49:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: (1 inline comment)

commit_message:
VMware: support the hotplug of a neutron port

Nova already has support for hotplugging neutorn ports in the libvirt
driver. This extends the support to the VMware driver.

Implements the blueprint vmware-hot-plug

Change-Id: I01b78621016e20c8e61d48bdeeac166f08f799be

commit_message:
Run integration tests full screen

I added self.driver.maximize_window() to helpers's setUp,
making all integration tests run full screen (maximizing
the browser's window).

Closes-Bug: #1338630
Change-Id: Idd185ef3a29eb4731d35fa957bf1e7d636237dc8

commit_message:
Stop coercing provider res. attributes to strings

Attributes of a resource defined in another template were
automatically converted to a string. If a provider resource returned
{"ip": ..., "name": ...} as an attribute value, it was converted to
"{'ip': ..., 'name': ...}".

This fix makes the behaviour consistent with the way stack outputs and
native resource work (i.e. can return strings, lists and maps).

Closes-Bug: #1297938
Change-Id: I7f27910e0ec877738998ff80c44e12d3bd4bfa7b

commit_message:
Fix IDP commands

identity_client.identity_providers doesn't exist as a manager. These are
located at identity_client.federation.identity_providers. Fix the
routes.

Also fix passing id to .create() as a positional argument. This is not
allowed from keystoneclient it should be passed as a keyword argument.

Change-Id: I912c27fcee58b0723e27e9147def2cbd1c62c288

a metadata block to provide information about the instance
that is being run. When querying the libvirt guest XML this
is visible thus:

<domain type='kvm' id='6'>
  <name>instance-00000004</name>
  <uuid>a173eb64-f8e6-419b-a2b7-2d3283ecb26c</uuid>
  <metadata>
    <nova:instance xmlns:nova="http://openstack.org/xmlns/libvirt/nova/1.0">
      <nova:package version="2014.2"/>
      <nova:name>demo</nova:name>
      <nova:creationTime>2014-06-27 11:22:25+GMT</nova:creationTime>
      <nova:flavor name="m1.small">
        <nova:memory>2048</nova:memory>
        <nova:disk>20</nova:disk>
        <nova:swap>0</nova:swap>
        <nova:vcpus>1</nova:vcpus>
      </nova:flavor>
      <nova:owner>
        <nova:user uuid="18509018d00743c89518135e476003e0">admin</nova:user>
        <nova:project uuid="38bd8e984a3e435a87e950a441ee55aa">admin</nova:project>
      </nova:owner>
      <nova:root type="image" uuid="f0f0d38c-0a5f-4c54-83e5-d48006b888a7"/>

commit_message:
libvirt: define XML schema for recording nova instance metadata

Define an XML schema to be used in the libvirt guest config as
a metadata block to provide information about the instance
that is being run. When querying the libvirt guest XML this
is visible thus:

<domain type='kvm' id='6'>
  <name>instance-00000004</name>
  <uuid>a173eb64-f8e6-419b-a2b7-2d3283ecb26c</uuid>
  <metadata>
    <nova:instance xmlns:nova="http://openstack.org/xmlns/libvirt/nova/1.0">
      <nova:package version="2014.2"/>
      <nova:name>demo</nova:name>
      <nova:creationTime>2014-06-27 11:22:25+GMT</nova:creationTime>
      <nova:flavor name="m1.small">
        <nova:memory>2048</nova:memory>
        <nova:disk>20</nova:disk>
        <nova:swap>0</nova:swap>
        <nova:vcpus>1</nova:vcpus>
      </nova:flavor>
      <nova:owner>
        <nova:user uuid="18509018d00743c89518135e476003e0">admin</nova:user>
        <nova:project uuid="38bd8e984a3e435a87e950a441ee55aa">admin</nova:project>
      </nova:owner>
      <nova:root type="image" uuid="f0f0d38c-0a5f-4c54-83e5-d48006b888a7"/>
    </nova:instance>
  </metadata>
  ...snip...
</domain>

Blueprint: libvirt-driver-domain-metadata
Change-Id: I19432cb93bc1471118d9d323c712cdd9756a5926

commit_message:
Add API schema for v2.1/v3 reset_server_state API

By defining the API schema, it is possible to separate the validation
code from the API method. The API method can be more simple.
In addition, a response of API validation error can be consistent for
the whole Nova API.

Partially implements blueprint v3-api-schema

Change-Id: Ib6bf4d1f1d875249d1758d4414377d47e15a3198

commit_message:
Libvirt: Added suffix to configdrive_path required for rescue

It was observed that during nova rescue, nova failed to create
a rescue disk for disk.config. The reason being that .rescue
suffix was missing from the configdrive path. It was working
till Havana but the functionality broke in Icehouse. This commit
fixes the suffix problem.

Unittests have been added to verify following scenarios:
    1. Make sure that .rescue disks are created when not using
        config drive
    2. Make sure that .rescue disks are created when using
        config drive

Closes-Bug: #1334024

Change-Id: I87449ffddd047cb84b7b881757ea4c29927b95da

I've just followed the doc :) Now, maybe the code is right and the doc should be updated, instead.

This being said, if you look at the bug report in the commit log, you'll see that if you pause a rescued instance, then unpause it, you do not go back to the "RESCUED" state, but to the "ACTIVE" state, which is probably not what you want.'}, {'account_id': 9275, 'date': '2014-05-20 12:22:46.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

@Garyk,

1) If you pause the instance and unpause, then it become ACTIVE so it's not possible to unrescue anymore.
2) The same happen as (1) with STOP

Unless we save the rescued state on that operations or allow unrescue to be more flexible ( but , you need to remember the real state the vm was before ), then it's not possible to unrescue anymore.

Those current limit, impose that if you want to change Vm states of rescued, then you should unrescue first.

any other idea?"}, {'account_id': 7020, 'date': '2014-05-20 13:26:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

@garyk: Fwiw, this diagram shows that a VM in a RESCUED state can only do 3 actions:

 + delete
 + reboot
 + unrescue

http://docs.openstack.org/developer/nova/devref/vmstates.html

If we decide to allow pausing and stopping a RESCUED instance, we should also update these docs.'}, {'account_id': 9275, 'date': '2014-05-20 13:28:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

commit_message:
VM in rescue state must have a restricted set of actions

Right now it is possible to pause, suspend and stop a VM in state RESCUED,
so after the state is changed, it's not possible to trigger unrescue anymore
since the original state is lost.

This patch remove vm_states.RESCUED as valid state from stop,
pause and suspend actions.

The vm_states devref is also updated to reflect this change including the
current reboot flow.( vm_states.RESCUED cannot be rebooted as per
today code)

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1319182
Co-Authored-By: Cyril Roelandt <cyril.roelandt@enovance.com>
Change-Id: I531dea5a5499bf93c24bea37850d562134dee281

commit_message:
Separate the console scripts

Having all the console scripts in one file means that we always pull
in all the dependencies. This presents a problem in downstream packaging,
for example, a distro alarm subpackage required pymongo dependencies
installed, even if not used.

This patch separates the console scripts into a 'cmd' module, the
way Nova does it. Eventlet monkey patching is done in the module's
__init__.py file.

Co-Authored-By: Mehdi Abaakouk <mehdi.abaakouk@enovance.com>
Closes-bug: #1317210
Change-Id: I83020b13670928fd0d3046d2d2a493b11fe81d61

subject: Use immutable arg rather mutable arg

commit_message:
Use immutable arg rather mutable arg

Passing mutable objects as default args is a known Python pitfall.
We'd better avoid this. This commit changes mutable default args with
None, then use 'arg = arg or []'.

Change-Id: I52a37bbc129fab40a99c919a837147d663941dce

commit_message:
[EDP] Using trust delegation for Swift authentication

For access to Swift objects, Sahara should be changed to generate a
Keystone trust between the user with access to those objects and the
Sahara admin user. The trust would be established based on the user’s
membership in the project that contains the Swift objects. Using this
trust the Sahara user could generate authentication tokens to access the
Swift objects. When access is no longer needed the trust can be revoked
thus invalidating the tokens.

blueprint edp-swift-trust-authentication

Change-Id: Ia48cd573f4c3ca9a7cbe1edb652f7a27b03615f9

But for multiple string option, it is better to set default values, as the value in nova.conf will be simply overwrite the default value in nova but not appending the value.'}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2014-04-28 20:13:12.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

I agree with Sean. devstack shouldn't set default values, even for multi string options, which are a little strange themselves."}, {'account_id': 7494, 'date': '2014-04-29 03:12:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

This will bring some trouble for developers who is using devstack.

I think that multi string options should be treated as an exception for devstack, it was now bring trouble to climate and may bring trouble to other projects in future. The devstack should make less trouble to developers.

Also I do not know why not remove the default values such as force_dhcp_release, instance_name_template etc as we also already have default value for those attributes.'}, {'account_id': 7494, 'date': '2014-07-22 09:20:21.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Set osapi_compute_extensions default value

The Devstack commit 3317437caca5eb769ab4c6d3ea7c5d3e062517e2 removed
the osapi_compute_extensions configuration option from lib/nova.

This caused a bug of Climate 1312368, I think that we should not remove
default value of osapi_compute_extension from devstack in nova as this
value is a multiple string option. Once the default value is removed,
then when we add another value of osapi_compute_extension in nova.conf,
the default value of nova.api.openstack.compute.contrib.standard_extensions
will be overwritted and this will causes a lot of HTTP 404 at Nova API.

Change-Id: I828cb331dfb578889c66eff6ed76bde6be65b20c

commit_message:
Storm Integration

This blueprint aims to implement Storm as a processing option in Sahara.
Storm is a real time processing framework that is highly used in the big
data processing community.

Implements: blueprint storm-integration

commit_message:
Fix nova/pci direct use of object modules

This replaces all uses of nova.objects.<module>.<object> with
nova.objects.<object> within nova/pci and nova/tests/pci.

Change-Id: I72e763fb5032a5dc2cf649e5e29213ea71578c8d
Partial-Blueprint: object-subclassing

commit_message:
VMware: Remove unnecessary deepcopy()s in test_configdrive

test_configdrive was doing a deepcopy of its test_instance object in
some tests. This was unnecessary, as the object is created fresh in
setUp().

Also, change a couple of dict lookups of test_instance to object
properties.

Change-Id: I3a5039fde9f8fba5285d90b28743b7af8cd1a168

commit_message:
Fix updating for OS::Neutron::Port resource

Updating of port resource should not lead to removing ip address.
This patch includes next changes:
- Fix update behavior for Port resource.
- Using properties names instead of constant names.
- New test was added for port create/update actions.

Change-Id: Iff73aaaa433ac56515a931f83ad201d15fca2bd8
Closes-Bug: #1343166

commit_message:
Remove the random string from instance logs

The random string being part of the path where logs are stored may cause
complications when trying to tell logstash what to index.

Change-Id: Ie84492ab981b06421d486579fc269ef6b3ad1815

My two cents:

So you must be referring to usage of SELECT FOR UPDATE statements here which can result in deadlocks. The way I see it is that unlike the situation when locks are acquired implicitly (e.g. when you update rows concurrently from different transactions) issuing of SELECT FOR UPDATE statements is pretty well defined. So instead of retrying the transaction until it succeeds, I'd really like to see this fixed in the first place by ensuring SELECT FOR UPDATE acquires locks in some defined order.

This is really not a "we are not going to merge this ever", but rather "can we at least try to fix this first"'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-05-22 10:11:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

Hi Roman, thanks for your reviewing.

Here's a protection for 'Query' object like 'Session' has.
Now the 'Query' object has been widely used for querying something in the system. So, any imprecise/loose usages may occur deadlock especially in a large-scale environments. But we can't assume the deadlock won't happen and we could identify them in reviewing or code-reading.
So, I think we need to add it to be a protection mechanism here.

Moreover, the related bug for the deadlock in nova has been merged in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/88081/. :)

Thanks."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-06-27 15:03:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: -Verified

commit_message:
Add protection for Query deadlock in sqlalchemy

The function '@_wrap_db_error' and '@retry_on_dead_lock',
is only available for session deadlock(query/flush/execute).

But it doesn't cover some 'Query' actions.
So, we need to add the same protection for 'all()' in sqlalchemy.

Change-Id: Ibd9847ec40ff0b4fa2ee2a36a2ea728771ade80b
Closes-Bug: #1283987

commit_message:
Read glance protocol, port for glance_api_servers

Currently glance_api_servers is being in nova.conf set as
    glance_host:9292
It should be:
    glance_protocol://glance_host:glance_port
to allow inclusion of SSL setting (of https) for protocol

Currently glance_port is hardcoded and protocol is assumed,
this change reads the value set in the yaml configuration file.

Change to the yaml file to put the value in as configurable is:
    I3c7218292797c62c36e2aaab4f325bf053ef140b

Depends on: I5fe952f850339465de128e56e45c9bbda011ce7f

commit_message:
Refactor Galera module

- Implements clustercheck script
- Switch haproxy to clustercheck
- Refactor Galera module
- Fix linting
- Add Rakefile, Gemfile
- Add more settings to wsrep.conf
- Update Modulefile

Change-Id: I14aaf056ec7a086ae07ab699bcb9b8f1403d8490
Implements: bp/galera-improvements

commit_message:
Xen: Cleanup orphan volume connections on boot failure

If the boot process fails after the VDI creation but before a VBD is
created then the current cleanup methods will not work as they all rely
on lookups via VBD.

Change-Id: Id0d93ee60f75bf319baf7859b220ca325175128a
Closes-bug: #1329941

commit_message:
Enable live migration unit test use instance object

test_post_live_migration_no_shared_storage_working_correctly is
still using instance dict, we should change it to using instance

This patch LGTM, however, I am blocking for two reasons:

- this patch series doesn't have a spec. Even though this direction was agreed upon during Icehouse and most of the code was written before we adopted the specs process, I'd like there to be a spec that describes what we agreed upon. It should be easy for me to approve it, but it needs to be there to document the changes.

- this whole patch series needs to land at once. Partial changes to some drivers will be very detrimental without the corresponding API changes, which are at the tail of this patch series, and are NOT approved yet.

I will remove this block once the whole patch series has been +2/+A'd.

Cheers!

commit_message:
IPMITool to use the new ManagementInterface

Add the new ManagementInterface to the IPMITool driver. The method
set_boot_device was removed from the VendorPassthru interface because
this method was promoved to the ManagementInterface.

Implements: blueprint new-management-interface
Change-Id: I7bd9cb0a5d38f1044ae3e74dd08564e20828933b

commit_message:
libvirt: remove unused list_instance_ids method

All code has been converted to use list_instance_domains so the
list_instance_ids method can finally be removed.

Blueprint: libvirt-domain-listing-speedup
Change-Id: I9ce33cda5608796e0eec4ec0804ee179a4704d9d

commit_message:
Make hypervisor_version an int in fakeVirt driver

This is a follow up to 9e770e62135fe9c2c8ac0121a5a79245b25a7847, which
missed the change in a duplicate copy of host_status.

Add regression test to test_virt_drivers.

This requires changes to the API samples, because they were wrong. virt
drivers use convert_version_to_int which converts a version string to a
4 digit number ("1.0" becomes to 1000)

Change-Id: I28ce23509e3c9feae183a49a8fc5bf3c7c601295
Closes-Bug: #1285035

commit_message:
Set glance control_exchange to 'glance'

Glance control_exchange in glance-api.conf wasn't set
and glance used default value for this - 'openstack'.
So, exchange 'glance' and queue 'glance' didn't exist in rabbit.
But ceilometer as default glance control exchange uses 'glance'.
This patch fixes the fix for this problem and change-id as well

Closes-bug: #1335891

Change-Id: Ia1891593f57de6533da0479074423fd0b73e7f52

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-07-18 18:29:17.000000000', 'message': "Security hardening: fix possible shell injection vulnerability

The glance/cmd/control.py file contains a possible shell injection
vulnerability:

https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/cmd/control.py#L134 .

Setting 'shell=True' here opens the possibility of shell injection
by setting server to something like '; rm -rf /'. This will cause
the command 'rm -rf /' to be run with the privileges of the user
that ran Glance.

The fix is to parameterize the input so that the command run here
can only be 'logger'.

Change-Id: If48106ceea1dd582bcec9d03e056d88591bcba8d
Closes-bug: 1335208
"}, {'created': '2014-07-21 15:20:25.000000000', 'message': "Security hardening: fix possible shell injection vulnerability

commit_message:
Security hardening: fix possible shell injection vulnerability

The glance/cmd/control.py file contains a possible shell injection
vulnerability:

https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/cmd/control.py#L134 .

Setting 'shell=True' here opens the possibility of shell injection
by setting server to something like '; rm -rf /'. This will cause
the command 'rm -rf /' to be run with the privileges of the user
that ran Glance.

The fix is to parameterize the input so that the command run here
can only be 'logger'.

Change-Id: If48106ceea1dd582bcec9d03e056d88591bcba8d
Closes-bug: 1335208

commit_message:
expose glance_port,protocol as glance.port,protocol

These values are available in metadata with underscores but
they are accessed by nova with dots.
Make them available with dots.

Required by: Idccc0d60c9f6b17a853c6de1bbea64bfc7e028b2
Change-Id: I5fe952f850339465de128e56e45c9bbda011ce7f

commit_message:
Setup for translation

To start translation, we need to initially import the
translation file - and place it at the proper place so that
the usual CI scripts can handle it.

The proper place is for all python projects
$PROJECT/locale/$PROJECT.pot - see setup.cfg.

Further imports will be done by the OpenStack Proposal bot.

bp graduate-oslo.utils
Change-Id: I270753ebd205e86a4a04225f74d6d40f4253e21c

commit_message:
Warn on tiny subnet

Log a warning when a user creates a /32 IPv4 subnet since
it will be useless.

Closes-Bug: #1341040
Change-Id: I6a39919e7ce4a39ba67f1ca79e55708566c086fc

commit_message:
Use opportunistic approach for migration testing

Refactored migration tests due to use OpportunisticTestCase, removed
unused code and ``test_migrations.conf`` file.

This change allows tests use database ``openstack_citest`` only
for connection to the database backend. The main feature of this
approach is - for each migration test will be created new database
with random name. This will avoid migration tests of race conditions
and reduce tests intersection.

``test_migrations.conf`` file was removed, because we create test
database for migration test, so we no longer need test database credentials.

Closes-Bug: #1327397
Closes-Bug: #1328997

Change-Id: I95ad140ba5f483cd3dc36e2b78f140826d57624f

'}, {'account_id': 8968, 'date': '2014-01-28 14:45:33.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(4 inline comments)

Thanks for the patch! Good start

I left comments regarding test naming inline. In general I'd like to see the following naming convention:

1. test_list_ports, test_create_port, test_delete_port - represent GET, POST and DELETE methods.

2. test_update_port_replace, test_update_port_add, test_update_port_remove, test_update_port_mixed_ops - represent possible contents of UPDATE method (jsonpatch operations)

3. for negative tests: test_update_port_replace_mac_with_duplicated (this is about PATCH replace op with duplicate value), test_update_port_by_mac_not_allowed (this is about the accessing resource by non_allowed url, e.g. UPDATE to ports/mac/ instead of ports/uuid/), test_create_port_no_mandatory_field_mac, test_update_port_remove_mandatory_field_mac, test_update_port_remove_mandatory_field_uuid and like this.

Please do not use ADDRESS in test names, because it's not clear what address is meant. I suggest to always use MAC.
Please do not use invalid_mac or so, because it's not clear what exactly is tested. Instead I suggest to use duplicate, malformed (for bad format), nonexistent, e.g test_create_port_duplicate_mac, test_create_port_nonexistent_node_id, test_create_port_malformed_mac.

Sorry, it may seem a bit complex, but if we won't follow some clear naming convention I'm pretty sure we'll lost some tests. Please rename existing tests according to my suggestions, feel free to change names that I proposed inline if you see that they are not clear or not strictly fit into proposed convention. Also the order of tests is important to not to miss anything. Please try to follow the suggestion below.

With that said here is my vision of the complete test suite for ports:

POSITIVE:
test_list_ports
test_list_port_details
test_list_with_limit
test_list_with_links

test_show_port
test_show_port_with_links

test_create_port
test_create_port_specifying_uuid
test_create_port_with_extra

test_update_port_add (I think we can test only multi if multi is possible, otherwise only single)
test_update_port_remove (same)
test_update_port_replace (same)
test_update_port_mixed_ops

test_delete_port

NEGATIVE:
test_list_port_details_against_single

test_show_port_malformed_uuid
test_show_port_nonexistent_uuid
test_show_port_by_mac_not_allowed

test_create_port_duplicated_port_uuid
test_create_port_malformed_port_uuid
test_create_port_invalid_extra
test_create_port_no_mandatory_field_node_id
test_create_port_malformed_node_id
test_create_port_nonexsistent_node_id
test_create_port_no_mandatory_field_mac
test_create_port_malformed_mac
test_create_port_duplicate_mac

test_update_port_nonexistent
test_update_port_malformed_port_uuid
test_update_port_by_mac_not_allowed
test_update_port_add_invalid_extra
test_update_port_add_whole_invalid_extra
test_update_port_add_nonexistent_property
test_update_port_replace_mac_with_duplicate
test_update_port_replace_mac_with_malformed
test_update_port_replace_node_id_with_nonexistent
test_update_port_replace_node_id_with_malformed
test_update_port_replace_whole_extra_with_invalid
test_update_port_replace_extra_item_with_invalid
test_update_port_replace_nonexistent_property
test_update_port_remove_mandatory_field_port_uuid
test_update_port_remove_mandatory_field_mac
test_update_port_remove_nonexistent_property
test_update_port_mixed_ops_integrity (assume the last operation in patch is bad, let's test if other ones were not applied. E.g patch applied completely if all valid, not applied at all if at least one invalid)

test_delete_port_nonexistent
test_delete_port_by_mac_not_allowed

Meanwhile I'm going to update my patch for chassis according to this comment as well :D"}, {'account_id': 8968, 'date': '2014-01-28 14:47:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Expose an entry point to list auth_token middleware config options

Register a 'keystoneclient.middleware.auth_token' entry point in the
oslo.config.opts namespace which, when called, returns a list of the
configuration options which may be registered by the project at runtime.

The idea here is that the sample config file generator can query this
and include the returned options in the sample config file of any
applications which use the middleware, e.g. currently the options
were listed in 'keystone_authtoken' section for those major projects.

Related-Change-Id: I15686708fc9460948a58cfea3d18dae40ba1fda9
Related-Change-Id: Ic28351258652d2ea38974e2f4d1aa6b1d3dd7192
Related-Change-Id: Iae31856d5886ee78786972d80c7c103c3460a2b3
Related-Bug: #1300546

Change-Id: I76043b08e2872867e5af2a5ac902e4d092fda5c8
Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>

commit_message:
merge.py use a class to represent template syntax

Defining cfn template syntax as class attributes will make it easier
to port merge.py to HOT just by setting lang to a different class.

Change-Id: I2547333d727bf91cd3159790f0f20f4d10195a9c
Partial-Blueprint: tripleo-juno-remove-mergepy

commit_message:
The default value of quota_firewall_rule should not be -1

A bad tenant User can create unlimited firewall rules to
"attack" the network node, so I modify the default value to 100.

Change-Id: I485c24cb1a7ed77dee81356fe6d95276808a47d4
Closes-Bug: #1346372

commit_message:
feat(v1.1): Default TTL and grace values

When posting messages, the "ttl" field may be omitted, in which
case the server defaults to the default TTL value configured by
the operator.

Likewise, when creating a claim, the "ttl" and "grace" fields
may be omitted to use the defaults configured for each field.

Change-Id: I38c6307377293b26370de28ffa13db22228c208c
Partially-Implements: blueprint api-v1.1-request-document-changes

commit_message:
Cleanup: remove unused argument

The vm_util.get_values_from_object_properties(...) method in the VMware
driver takes an unused param 'properties'.

This patch cleans up the method signature.

Change-Id: Iba738c2b49f829c1c0e17973b5265e88741fade7

commit_message:
Control update, delete for cisco-network-profile

Add new behavior to control update and delete operations for the
cisco-network-profile resource extension.
The new behavior is to allow update and delete operations only if
there are no neutron networks associated with a particular
cisco-network-profile instance

Change-Id: I000a03c1ffd5c02e7b827ec757287633e5a5dd64
Closes-Bug: #1323867
(cherry picked from commit accd56fea86a0cd5f1706cbdd5b1bbc31c4cf479)

commit_message:
Suppress outputs in test_cli20_nsx_networkgateway

The output is from argparse and we need to capture stderr in
setUp(). oslotest.base.BaseTestCase is used as the base class
of test_cli20 to setup stdout/stderr capture.

Closes-Bug: #1296151
Change-Id: I86c50efcf451242c2c1ec13ac5def19d82c1e172

commit_message:
Removes useless stub of glanceclient create

There was a stub out of glanceclient.create that was being called from a
couple unit test setUp()'s, but the stub method stubs out something that
is overridden by the stub_out_glance() fake method.

Change-Id: I300f6ccc999958c33a2dd729cb8bde89bed63967

commit_message:
VMware: remove unused parameter 'network_info'

The parameter 'network_info' is not used for destroying an instance and
doesn't need to be passed through the whole stack.

Change-Id: I0a8b912ff7693478917e849e17093d1541adeeeb

Currently after attach interface failed, the allocated port still existed
and bind with the instance. This patch try to cleanup the port after attach
failed.

Change-Id: Iedcef2961915e332acad43cc41aa173429be3b84
Closes-Bug: #1341498

commit_message:
Deallocated interface after attach interface failed

Currently after attach interface failed, the allocated port still existed
and bind with the instance. This patch try to cleanup the port after attach
failed.

Change-Id: Iedcef2961915e332acad43cc41aa173429be3b84
Closes-Bug: #1341498

commit_message:
Correct LOG.debug use

The commit b3202c3283597de031572e0ede082237487d8110 used:

  LOG.debug("...%(key1)s...", key1=value1)

which  is not supported, this change ues instead:

  LOG.debug("...%(key1)s...", {"key1": value1})

At first glance this looks like a featureful change rather than a bugfix. What issue does it solve for stable/icehouse users ?'}, {'account_id': 5293, 'date': '2014-07-21 06:14:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

@Thierry This adds the APIDocs to the repo. None of the actual code / bits shipped for packaging change. This cherry-pick adds the icehouse API docs (and not any subsequent updates since then). 

The reason we need this is because we added a few Infra jobs that run against trove to make sure that the API docs exist and build cleanly. This job runs against _all_ trove branches including stable/icehouse. Without this commit, this infra job fails, and since it is part of the gate, no other change can get through.

So we had two options:
1. Specialize the docs jobs so that they gate only on master and not stable/iceshouse, or
2. Cherry pick the API docs commit to the stable/icehouse branch, so that we can continue to run the docs gate job against all branches.

I chose to do the latter, and this patchset is a consequence of that.

Thanks!'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-21 17:00:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: -Verified

commit_message:
Moved the apidocs from openstack/database-api

By hosting the docs here we'll be able to better maintain that
developers are being mindful of changes or even occassionally writing
documentation for new API features. This should also allow us to
autogenerate the snippets.

Change-Id: I0111bcd38341b1736a47b0a3d3e6ff96d2ca1c58
(cherry picked from commit 294330c554eff8e2b120d2e4a2d39a44412de200)

commit_message:
libvirt: Support IPv6 with LXC

Libvirt's LXC implementation exposes a read-only  `/proc/sys/net` to the
guests. This causes some of the guest's default network configuration scripts
to fail.

This patch works-around the issue by using `post-up` hooks to configure IPv6.

Closes-Bug: 1340791

Change-Id: I805cad98d855fcb2c90b07e98ad3653d1620bd42

commit_message:
fix project quota showing error and success message

right now if you try to change a quota value to something less than what is currently
used, it will give you both error and success message
fix test cases to check for 2 errors messages

Change-Id: I25550346e553b1469b321cd46b2eeff612f11869

[{'created': '2014-07-17 19:21:51.000000000', 'message': 'Fix Cells ImagePropertiesFilter can raise exceptions

In a misconfigured scenario the ImagePropertiesFilter can raise an
exception which causes the image to be unbuildable in the region. This

Change-Id: I17bd9d87fa69ad34b19591018543a34dfd050978
Closes-Bug: 1343462

commit_message:
Fix Cells ImagePropertiesFilter can raise exceptions

In a misconfigured scenario the ImagePropertiesFilter can raise an
exception which causes the image to be unbuildable in the region. This
happens when the capabilities is set for prominent_hypervisor_version
to an empty list.

Change-Id: I17bd9d87fa69ad34b19591018543a34dfd050978
Closes-Bug: 1343462

commit_message:
Make plugin deallocation check optional

The fix for memory leakage in the related bug added a check for plugin
deallocation that performed a call to gc.collect() after every test.
This had the side-effect of increasing test execution time by ~50%, so
this patch makes the check optional via an environment variable
(OS_CHECK_PLUGIN_DEALLOCATION).

It may make sense to create a periodic job that runs with the check
enabled, but otherwise the check can be used by developers for
debugging purposes.

Change-Id: I9ebe663abbc4e4ff3a62d807d5a3230c2ecccd07
Related-Bug: #1234857
(cherry picked from commit ee5c3b0bb60918a7e59e89ceffbafa2f683b74fd)

commit_message:
Fix context sensitive help for info and tempurl

Make it so that swift <cmd> --help will print the info
subcommand help for info and tempurl just like all the
other subcommands.

Also add unit tests to verify subcommand help.

Change-Id: Id3666dcf72a9727fbfda2f74c23293ada1c53aa0

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-06-24 19:50:28.000000000', 'message': 'Ensure core plugin deallocation after every test

The unit tests were previously consuming an excessive amount of memory
(4GB+) due to plugin instances persisting in memory.  Deallocation was
not possible where a combination of circular references and mocking
was involved.  This patch ensures that only NeutronManager holds a
plugin reference and that all other references are instances of
weakref.proxy.  Residual memory footprint for tox executed on a
12-core machine has been reduced to ~1.3GB.  Plugin deallocation is
validated at the end of each test to prevent regressions.

This change also includes fixes to unit tests that depended on plugin
instances persisting across tests.

Conflicts:

	neutron/tests/base.py
	neutron/tests/unit/ml2/test_mechanism_odl.py
	neutron/tests/unit/test_db_plugin.py

Partial-Bug: #1234857
Change-Id: Ia1f868c2d206eb72ef77d290d054f3c48ab58c94

commit_message:
Ensure core plugin deallocation after every test

The unit tests were previously consuming an excessive amount of memory
(4GB+) due to plugin instances persisting in memory.  Deallocation was
not possible where a combination of circular references and mocking
was involved.  This patch ensures that only NeutronManager holds a
plugin reference and that all other references are instances of
weakref.proxy.  Residual memory footprint for tox executed on a
12-core machine has been reduced to ~1.3GB.  Plugin deallocation is
validated at the end of each test to prevent regressions.

This change also includes fixes to unit tests that depended on plugin
instances persisting across tests.

Conflicts:

	neutron/tests/base.py
	neutron/tests/unit/ml2/test_mechanism_odl.py
	neutron/tests/unit/test_db_plugin.py

Partial-Bug: #1234857
Change-Id: Ia1f868c2d206eb72ef77d290d054f3c48ab58c94
(cherry picked from commit 6db48dd688d45ba41863926fa1a91d2d3ea484ec)
